The paper deals with the regularity problem and decidability of languages recognized by Parikh automata, which are related to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). It also involves vector addition systems, which are a type of data structure used in computer science and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The regular separability problem is a decision problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic (cs.LO). Finally, the paper mentions the use of information theory in their results (cs.IT).
